rules:
  - id: models.frameworks.model_card_structure
    description: |
      All model cards and framework documentation must strictly adhere to the standardized structure as presented in the Claude Sonnet 4.5 System Card (see: https://assets.anthropic.com/m/12f214efcc2f457a/original/Claude-Sonnet-4-5-System-Card.pdf). This structure includes, but is not limited to, the following required sections in the specified order:
        1. Title and Version
        2. Overview & Intended Use
        3. Capabilities
        4. Limitations
        5. Safety and Mitigations
        6. Training Data & Methodology
        7. Evaluation
        8. Monitoring & Maintenance
        9. Ethical Considerations
        10. References & Further Reading
      - Each section must be clearly labeled, comprehensive, and reflect the latest available information.
      - Deviations from this format are not permitted unless explicitly authorized by governance/architecture review.
      - When updating, ensure consistency throughout and promptly apply any new organizational documentation or regulatory requirements.
      - Rationales, design decisions, and risks must be documented wherever applicable.
      - Subsections or additional detail should mirror the depth and transparency exemplified in the cited system card.
    severity: error
    references:
      - https://assets.anthropic.com/m/12f214efcc2f457a/original/Claude-Sonnet-4-5-System-Card.pdf
